Besides crystal phase, introduction of C-dot also exhibited great influence on the morphology and structural feature of the products. As shown in Fig. 4
                        , all the synthesized S-C3N4/C-dot composites (Fig. 4c-f) exhibited similar bar-like structures, same as the pure S-C3N4 (S-0), indicating that the introduction of C-dot did not alter the integral structure of the S-C3N4 substrate. However, combined with N2 adsorption-desorption isotherms and pore size distribution analyses (Fig. 5
                        ), it can be easily concluded that, textural structure of the bars in different samples differ from each other dramatically.
